A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Part 5 of Article 6 of Chapter 2 of Title 20 of the Official Code of Georgia
2 Annotated, relating to program weights and funding requirements, so as to require that the
3 State Board of Education include instruction in the proper use of a school bus passenger
4 restraint system within its program of safety instruction; to amend Part 6 of Article 1 of
5 Chapter 8 of Title 40 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to equipment of
6 school buses, so as to require that school buses be equipped with passenger restraint systems;
7 to require that each school child wear a passenger restraint system in certain instances; to
8 provide for an exception; to authorize a penalty; to provide for a definition; to provide for the
9 promulgation of rules and regulations; to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting
10 laws; and for other purposes.
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
12 SECTION 1.
13 Part 5 of Article 6 of Chapter 2 of Title 20 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
14 relating to program weights and funding requirements, is amended by revising subsection (e)
15 of Code Section 20-2-188, relating to student transportation, as follows:
