16 "(e) The State Board of Education shall establish and require adherence to minimum
17 specifications for vehicles used or contracted to be used by local units of administration for
18 transporting students, including a motor vehicle with a capacity of eight persons or less
19 operated and marked for the transportation of school children to and from school and
20 school related activities, taking into account the factors and circumstances set forth in
21 subsection (a) of this Code section, and shall establish and require adherence to minimum
22 standards and requirements respecting maintenance, repair, inspection, and use of such
23 vehicles and minimum qualifications for the drivers of such vehicles. The state board State
24 Board of Education shall require, monitor, and fund a program of safety instruction in the
25 practices of safe riding, which shall include instruction in the proper use of a school bus
26 passenger restraint system in accordance with Code Section 40-8-111, and emergency bus
27 evacuation drills for both school bus drivers and students riding school buses."
28 SECTION 2.
29 Part 6 of Article 1 of Chapter 8 of Title 40 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
30 relating to equipment of school buses, is amended by revising Code Section 40-8-111,
31 relating to equipment generally, as follows:
32 "40-8-111.
33 (a) As used in this Code section, the term 'passenger restraint system' means:
34 (1) A type 2 seat belt assembly that is in compliance with Federal Motor Vehicle Safety
35 Standard 209 and with Federal Motor Vehicle Safety 210 as such standards were in effect
36 on the date the school bus was manufactured; or
37 (2) A type 2 lap and shoulder restraint system that is in compliance with Federal Motor
38 Vehicle Safety Standard 222.
39 (a)(b) Each school bus used for the transportation of school children in the State of
40 Georgia shall be in compliance with this state shall comply with the provisions of this Code
