41 section and the State Board of Education bus specifications for the model year of such
42 school bus.
43 (c)(1) On and after July 1, 2027:
44 (A) Each school bus manufactured and used for the transportation of school children
45 in this state shall be equipped with passenger restraint systems for each school child
46 based upon the maximum passenger capacity of the school bus; and
47 (B) The State Board of Education shall require each school child to wear a passenger
48 restraint system. Except as provided in paragraph (3) of this subsection, each such
49 child shall wear a passenger restraint system at all times while the school bus is in
50 motion.
51 (2) It shall be the responsibility of a school bus driver operating such school bus to
52 ensure that each such child being transported is wearing a passenger restraint system prior
53 to the school bus being placed into motion. A school child's parent or guardian shall not
54 be held liable for such child's failure to wear a passenger restraint system in accordance
55 with the provisions of subparagraph (c)(1)(B) of this Code section.
56 (3) A school child with a physically disabling condition or medical condition that
57 prevents appropriate restraint in a passenger restraint system shall not be required to wear
58 a passenger restraint system on a school bus; provided, however, that such child's
59 physically disabling or medical condition is certified in writing by a licensed healthcare
60 provider.
61 (b)(d) Each public school system shall be required to maintain each of its school buses in
62 good working condition, including all safety equipment required in accordance with the
63 specifications established pursuant to subsection (a) (b) of this Code section. A public
64 school system that fails to comply with such specifications may be subject to a penalty to
65 be determined by the State Board of Education.
